body:
iverilog (9dd99806ad2c2fb) reports several times the exact same error for this file:
```
module ssub(o);
output o;
endmodule

module sub;
reg x;
ssub i(x);
endmodule

module top;
sub i1();
sub i2();
endmodule
```
The error is triggered by and reported in module `sub`. The error is reported as many times as there are instances of `sub` in `top`.
```
test.v:7: error: reg x; cannot be driven by primitives or continuous assignment.
test.v:7: error: Output port expression must support continuous assignment.
test.v:7:      : Port 1 (o) of ssub is connected to x
